      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOW HIGH (6) jumped favourite and was too quick with an all-the-way win last start (25.34) at Shepparton in a Grade 5 over 450m. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. Looks the one to beat. KEY PHILOSOPHY (1) is a handy dog who jumped from box 7 last time out and scored by a long neck at The Meadows (30.25). The form out of last race has been strong. Should be in this for a long way. PAW ORTIZ (2) had a tricky draw last time when running fourth (29.91) over 515m at Sandown in a Grade 5. Solid record at the distance winning six races. Has ability and is one of the better chances. RIVERS MEET (7) is always hard to beat when he races here at this trip.",
